<!--....................................................................
|									|
|	hy-concept							|
|									|
|	Basic building block for knowledge base representation;  a	|
|	node in a knowledge base.  Expresses a relationship between	|
|	a pair of (possibly aggregate) anchors.				|
|									|
|	The anchrole attribute provides the semantic for a hy-term /	|
|	hy-desc pair.  It can be #FIXED;  could be one of the following	|
|	pairs of SKNs (or define more using dav.srdef-form elements).	|
|	Either or both SKNs could be characterized as potential		|
|	aggregates in the usual HyTime fashion (by using #AGG		|
|	immediately following the affected SKN).   Valid pairs:		|
|									|
|		symbol		value					|
|		item		descript				|
|		item		idItem					|
|		item		eqItem					|
|		item		simItem					|
|		item		oppItem					|
|		item		relItem					|
|		instance	class					|
|		subset		superset				|
|		portion		whole					|
|		owner		possessn				|
|		synopsis	expansn					|
|									|
|	The asrdgis attribute names one or more generic identifiers of	|
|	elements used to define the SKNs that appear in the value of	|
|	the anchrole attribute.  Default: any SKNs defined for anchor	|
|	roles by the SOFABED standard and any SKNs defined in the	|
